# DOCX Template Generation Skill

This project uses `@eigenpal/docx-template-skill` to convert example DOCX files into reusable docxtemplater templates.

## Tools

- `node skill/agent/dist/analyze.js <file.docx>` — Extract document structure as JSON
- `node skill/agent/dist/generate.js <original.docx> <mapping.json> [output.docx]` — Create template
- `node skill/agent/dist/refine.js <template.docx> <mods.json> [output.docx]` — Modify template
- `bun run preview` — Launch split-pane preview

## Workflow: Analyze → Generate → Refine

1. Always analyze first: `node skill/agent/dist/analyze.js examples/<file>.docx`
2. Build `field-mapping.json` from analysis + user input
3. Generate: `node skill/agent/dist/generate.js examples/<file>.docx field-mapping.json templates/<output>.docx`
4. Create `sample_data.json` with matching test data
5. Refine if needed with `modifications.json`

## Rules

- Read `skill/AGENT_INSTRUCTIONS.md` for full details
- Use camelCase for template tags
- `{#loop}{/loop}` for arrays, `{#bool}{/bool}` for conditionals
- Loop tags go inside table cells (first cell opens, last cell closes)
- Always create sample_data.json for validation
